This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the synthesis of photo-realistic food meal images. Additionally, it involves the use of generative deep models, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. 

The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) as it generates images from textual descriptions of ingredients. Therefore, it could also belong to the NLP (cs.CL) sub-category. 

The use of generative neural networks (GANs) and attention-based models suggests that the paper could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper involves the synthesis of complex images, which could require knowledge of graphics and visualization techniques. Therefore, it could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
